1
00:00:06,600 --> 00:00:11,537
=The Moment I Met You=

2
00:00:11,537 --> 00:00:14,937
=Episode 14=

3
00:00:16,359 --> 00:00:17,800
Xu Anran knows who you are.

4
00:00:18,359 --> 00:00:19,440
It was my oversight.

5
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:20,640
I thought

6
00:00:20,640 --> 00:00:22,640
he was just a bookish fool.

7
00:00:23,359 --> 00:00:24,480
In the Gate Bureau,

8
00:00:24,480 --> 00:00:26,519
no one is ever just a simple nerd.

9
00:00:27,839 --> 00:00:28,640
Still,

10
00:00:30,039 --> 00:00:31,039
I believe what he said.

11
00:00:33,399 --> 00:00:36,399
You think he won't betray us?

12
00:00:37,479 --> 00:00:39,640
If he wanted to,
he would have done it by now.

13
00:00:40,119 --> 00:00:41,439
I never would have guessed.

14
00:00:41,439 --> 00:00:42,200
This Xu Anran

15
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:44,159
looks so dim-witted,

16
00:00:44,479 --> 00:00:46,039
but he's actually quite calculating.

17
00:00:47,359 --> 00:00:48,240
I hope you're right.

18
00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:49,880
Chang,

19
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:52,359
we have to be
even more careful from now on.

20
00:00:54,640 --> 00:00:55,880
If Mao Buyu

21
00:00:56,200 --> 00:00:58,439
were as sharp as his brother-in-law,

22
00:00:59,679 --> 00:01:01,679
the two of you might
actually find happiness.

23
00:01:01,799 --> 00:01:02,799
Things are good as is.

24
00:01:03,479 --> 00:01:05,680
I think Buyu is just fine as he is.

25
00:01:05,680 --> 00:01:07,159
He's perfect for me.

26
00:01:08,200 --> 00:01:09,000
Oh, you.

27
00:01:22,640 --> 00:01:24,480
This is an ominous sign.

28
00:01:25,599 --> 00:01:28,920
(Thousand-Hand Titan, Dongfang Qing)
So you're saying both my disciples

29
00:01:29,359 --> 00:01:31,719
fell at the hands of the Jade Squirrel?

30
00:01:31,719 --> 00:01:32,319
Yes.

31
00:01:32,719 --> 00:01:34,247
Even if the Jade Squirrel

32
00:01:34,248 --> 00:01:35,959
(Wu Buzhi, Taoist Mystic)
didn't kill them personally,

33
00:01:36,159 --> 00:01:38,799
she is definitely involved.

34
00:01:40,120 --> 00:01:41,439
In this life,

35
00:01:41,760 --> 00:01:43,560
one must never take a wrong step.

36
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:44,900
Otherwise,

37
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:47,760
you'll live with regret forever.

38
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:50,319
As a former sect leader, are you saying

39
00:01:50,760 --> 00:01:52,239
you regret

40
00:01:52,239 --> 00:01:54,480
teaming up with those three brothers

41
00:01:54,480 --> 00:01:57,680
to seize the Sacred Token back then?

42
00:01:58,200 --> 00:02:01,680
Wu Buzhi, you truly live up to your name.

43
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:07,879
Actually, one thing still puzzles me.

44
00:02:08,319 --> 00:02:11,199
As the former leader
of the Southern Thieves,

45
00:02:11,199 --> 00:02:14,360
you shouldn't fear revenge
from the Sacred Hand Sect.

46
00:02:14,840 --> 00:02:18,000
Especially now that
Chu Zhongtian is dead.

47
00:02:18,520 --> 00:02:21,919
Yet you chose
to fake your death and hide away,

48
00:02:22,159 --> 00:02:23,400
moving from place to place.

49
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:24,199
Tell me,

50
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:26,840
why is that?

51
00:02:27,159 --> 00:02:29,319
Because I'm afraid of someone else.

52
00:02:31,439 --> 00:02:34,240
My biggest regret

53
00:02:34,759 --> 00:02:36,479
was ever collaborating with that man.

54
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:40,680
The Sacred Token is a hot potato now.

55
00:02:40,879 --> 00:02:41,960
If I reveal it,

56
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:44,520
everyone will want a piece of it.

57
00:02:45,879 --> 00:02:47,360
But keeping it hidden

58
00:02:48,080 --> 00:02:50,520
makes it as useless as scrap metal.

59
00:03:04,439 --> 00:03:05,080
Constable Mao.

60
00:03:05,960 --> 00:03:06,639
You may rise.

61
00:03:09,387 --> 00:03:11,626
Any progress
on the location of the Sacred Token?

62
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:12,520
Your Majesty.

63
00:03:13,199 --> 00:03:14,039
I have failed you.

64
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:16,400
I haven't found any sign of it yet.

65
00:03:17,800 --> 00:03:20,199
But there is something
I don't understand.

66
00:03:20,879 --> 00:03:22,750
It's just a token
from the Martial World.

67
00:03:22,879 --> 00:03:24,520
Why do you care so much about it?

68
00:03:26,439 --> 00:03:29,879
After the former
Grandmaster united the Martial World,

69
00:03:30,080 --> 00:03:31,520
it was bestowed by the late Emperor.

70
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:33,919
Forged from Tianshan Black Iron,

71
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:35,800
it was split into two pieces.

72
00:03:36,520 --> 00:03:39,000
Two tokens shaped
like a left and right hand.

73
00:03:39,680 --> 00:03:40,680
Whoever holds them

74
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:43,280
can command the entire Martial World.

75
00:03:50,212 --> 00:03:53,025
(Token)

76
00:03:56,100 --> 00:03:56,300
(Token)

77
00:04:00,560 --> 00:04:01,520
Jade Squirrel!

78
00:04:06,039 --> 00:04:06,639
Water...

79
00:04:07,430 --> 00:04:08,479
- I need water.
- Madam!

80
00:04:08,599 --> 00:04:09,360
What's wrong?

81
00:04:09,560 --> 00:04:10,719
Water...

82
00:04:11,520 --> 00:04:12,680
Let me help you inside.

83
00:04:16,160 --> 00:04:17,519
(Chang told me to wait here.)

84
00:04:17,959 --> 00:04:19,079
(Why isn't she here yet?)

85
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:25,120
Thank you, young lady.

86
00:04:25,439 --> 00:04:26,519
I feel much better.

87
00:04:26,519 --> 00:04:27,319
That's good.

88
00:04:27,519 --> 00:04:28,199
Madam,

89
00:04:28,399 --> 00:04:30,040
how did you end up like this?

90
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:31,519
I'm from the South.

91
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:35,279
I came to the Capital
to find my granddaughters.

92
00:04:35,839 --> 00:04:37,759
But then I heard that they're...

93
00:04:40,240 --> 00:04:41,480
They are both gone.

94
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:43,000
I have no one left.

95
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:45,000
I was so thirsty and hungry

96
00:04:46,439 --> 00:04:49,879
that I collapsed in front of your shop.

97
00:04:50,839 --> 00:04:52,879
Both your granddaughters are gone?

98
00:04:53,079 --> 00:04:54,560
Did they leave the city?

99
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:56,519
What were their names?

100
00:04:56,519 --> 00:04:57,780
I could help you look for them.

101
00:04:59,560 --> 00:05:00,800
They didn't leave.

102
00:05:01,319 --> 00:05:03,879
They're dead.

103
00:05:07,759 --> 00:05:09,439
They must have been very young.
So how...

104
00:05:10,000 --> 00:05:11,600
Was it an illness?

105
00:05:11,959 --> 00:05:13,920
They were murdered.

106
00:05:17,079 --> 00:05:19,360
Madam, don't be sad.

107
00:05:19,920 --> 00:05:20,879
Who murdered them?

108
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:22,639
I know people in the Gate Bureau.

109
00:05:22,639 --> 00:05:23,800
I can help you look into it.

110
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,720
It was the Gate Bureau
who murdered them.

111
00:05:32,879 --> 00:05:34,560
I hope Chang isn't in trouble.

112
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:39,319
Your granddaughters...

113
00:05:40,060 --> 00:05:41,000
What were their names?

114
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:43,279
One was named Lin.

115
00:05:43,879 --> 00:05:45,160
The other was named Hu.

116
00:05:46,639 --> 00:05:47,639
Who exactly are you?

117
00:05:48,199 --> 00:05:50,199
You must have met them, right?

118
00:05:50,519 --> 00:05:52,040
Leader of the Sacred Hand Sect.

119
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:55,120
Turns out you have
such a compassionate heart.

120
00:05:56,120 --> 00:05:57,240
You're a man!

121
00:06:07,480 --> 00:06:09,839
Thousand-Hand Titan, Dongfang Qing.

122
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:13,480
So, you're still alive.

123
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:14,480
Jade Squirrel.

124
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:15,519
You took what was mine

125
00:06:15,519 --> 00:06:16,800
without saying a word.

126
00:06:16,800 --> 00:06:19,120
You clearly have
no respect for me at all.

127
00:06:19,360 --> 00:06:20,199
When you stole

128
00:06:20,199 --> 00:06:21,759
the Sacred Token from my grandfather,

129
00:06:21,879 --> 00:06:23,480
did you show my family any respect then?

130
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:24,720
Some things

131
00:06:24,959 --> 00:06:27,240
aren't as simple
as they appear on the surface.

132
00:06:31,439 --> 00:06:32,079
Chang.

133
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:33,040
Are you alright?

134
00:06:33,759 --> 00:06:35,160
Is that your lover outside?

135
00:06:35,519 --> 00:06:36,439
None of your business.

136
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:38,600
Hand over the Sacred Token
and I'll let you go.

137
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:39,199
Nonsense!

138
00:06:39,319 --> 00:06:41,160
You've already taken the Sacred Token!

139
00:06:42,639 --> 00:06:43,240
Chang.

140
00:06:43,240 --> 00:06:44,439
I know you're in there.

141
00:06:44,439 --> 00:06:45,790
You just won't come out and see me.

142
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:46,839
Chang!

143
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,120
I know you.

144
00:06:48,279 --> 00:06:50,240
You wouldn't just
break our promise for no reason.

145
00:06:50,839 --> 00:06:52,319
Something must have happened to you.

146
00:06:52,319 --> 00:06:53,162
(Yunchang Flower Shop)

147
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:54,439
Can you hear me?

148
00:06:54,439 --> 00:06:55,199
Open the door!

149
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:56,360
Chang!

150
00:06:58,439 --> 00:06:59,079
Chang!

151
00:07:02,319 --> 00:07:02,920
Chang!

152
00:07:03,360 --> 00:07:03,959
Chang!

153
00:07:04,959 --> 00:07:05,600
Chang!

154
00:07:12,360 --> 00:07:13,240
You're awake.

155
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:15,480
Where is Buyu?

156
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:18,959
If I'd known an enemy
would come looking for us,

157
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:20,240
I wouldn't have gone out.

158
00:07:20,240 --> 00:07:21,279
I would have stayed here.

159
00:07:22,399 --> 00:07:23,199
Where is Buyu?

160
00:07:23,720 --> 00:07:25,720
He was worried sick just now.

161
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:27,879
He almost called
every healer in the Capital

162
00:07:27,879 --> 00:07:29,439
to come and treat you.

163
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:31,079
It's lucky I was quick-witted.

164
00:07:31,399 --> 00:07:33,399
I bribed them to say

165
00:07:33,600 --> 00:07:34,839
that you were suffering from

166
00:07:35,079 --> 00:07:37,519
exhaustion and a lack of vital energy.

167
00:07:37,839 --> 00:07:39,519
Right now, Buyu is probably

168
00:07:40,399 --> 00:07:42,199
seeing the healer out.

169
00:07:43,199 --> 00:07:44,120
You really are clever.

170
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:45,279
Of course I am.

171
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:47,639
Who were you fighting earlier?

172
00:07:47,639 --> 00:07:49,079
Your inner energy is in total chaos.

173
00:07:50,879 --> 00:07:51,759
Chang, you're awake!

174
00:07:53,360 --> 00:07:54,279
You're finally awake.

175
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:56,959
I'll leave you two alone now.

176
00:07:59,199 --> 00:07:59,879
Chang.

177
00:08:00,020 --> 00:08:00,920
Are you feeling better?

178
00:08:01,399 --> 00:08:02,920
I didn't mean to break our promise.

179
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:04,000
I just wasn't feeling well.

180
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:04,759
I know.

181
00:08:05,319 --> 00:08:06,480
Zhizhi just told me that

182
00:08:06,879 --> 00:08:08,040
you've been working too hard.

183
00:08:08,680 --> 00:08:09,639
What have you been

184
00:08:09,639 --> 00:08:10,680
so busy with?

185
00:08:12,439 --> 00:08:15,680
It's all because of us.

186
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:20,480
Thank you for everything, Chang.

187
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:21,959
But don't you worry.

188
00:08:22,319 --> 00:08:23,920
I'll handle the wedding arrangements.

189
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:26,279
You have no idea how worried I was

190
00:08:26,279 --> 00:08:27,360
when you collapsed.

191
00:08:30,519 --> 00:08:32,159
You were that worried about me?

192
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:35,039
You're the person
I'm going to grow old with.

193
00:08:35,039 --> 00:08:36,320
How could I not be worried?

194
00:08:38,039 --> 00:08:38,759
Silly.

195
00:08:40,759 --> 00:08:41,759
As long as you're safe,

196
00:08:41,879 --> 00:08:43,320
that's all that matters to me.

197
00:08:50,919 --> 00:08:51,919
Auntie, Uncle.

198
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,399
It's so late, why aren't you in bed?

199
00:08:53,639 --> 00:08:55,000
Were you out with Mao Buyu again?

200
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:58,919
You two stayed up all night

201
00:08:58,919 --> 00:09:00,159
just to wait for me?

202
00:09:01,279 --> 00:09:02,960
If you want to talk about Buyu,

203
00:09:03,000 --> 00:09:04,159
there's nothing to discuss.

204
00:09:05,919 --> 00:09:08,639
It's not that we don't accept him.

205
00:09:08,919 --> 00:09:11,879
We're just wary
of his family's background.

206
00:09:12,759 --> 00:09:13,480
Indeed.

207
00:09:13,879 --> 00:09:15,240
After all, his family and ours

208
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:16,720
are like fire and water.

209
00:09:17,080 --> 00:09:17,919
What about him?

210
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:20,360
He and Xu Anran are getting along fine.

211
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:23,559
Xu Anran recognizes us as heroes.

212
00:09:23,759 --> 00:09:24,600
But Buyu?

213
00:09:24,799 --> 00:09:26,080
He's just a hothead.

214
00:09:26,279 --> 00:09:28,120
He sees everything in black and white.

215
00:09:28,639 --> 00:09:29,399
Think about it.

216
00:09:29,399 --> 00:09:31,159
If he ever discovered your identity,

217
00:09:31,440 --> 00:09:32,840
even if he didn't arrest you,

218
00:09:33,159 --> 00:09:34,080
with his personality,

219
00:09:34,279 --> 00:09:35,720
the guilt would eat him alive.

220
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:37,399
You have a point.

221
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:39,200
In that case...

222
00:09:40,120 --> 00:09:41,879
We cut him loose.

223
00:09:42,039 --> 00:09:43,000
Or we flip him.

224
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:44,120
Make him join our sect.

225
00:09:47,279 --> 00:09:48,320
How do we do that?

226
00:09:48,799 --> 00:09:49,639
Set a trap.

227
00:09:50,039 --> 00:09:51,190
Drag him into the mud with us.

228
00:09:52,720 --> 00:09:53,759
You're the expert at that.

229
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:55,639
Me?

230
00:10:03,320 --> 00:10:04,000
Buyu.

231
00:10:04,759 --> 00:10:05,440
Squire Mei.

232
00:10:05,639 --> 00:10:06,279
Off duty?

233
00:10:06,879 --> 00:10:07,600
Just finished.

234
00:10:08,159 --> 00:10:08,720
Come.

235
00:10:09,039 --> 00:10:10,879
Tea and storytelling are on me.

236
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:13,879
I wanted to see Chang at the shop first.

237
00:10:14,519 --> 00:10:16,279
She went to the South City flower market.

238
00:10:16,519 --> 00:10:17,590
Let's have some tea first.

239
00:10:17,759 --> 00:10:19,759
She might even be back
by the time we're done.

240
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:23,720
Well, all right then.

241
00:10:24,519 --> 00:10:26,200
Thank you for the invitation, Squire Mei.

242
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:28,080
Stop with the title.

243
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:28,840
Call me Uncle.

244
00:10:30,080 --> 00:10:31,159
Yes, Uncle.

245
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:32,399
This way.

246
00:10:32,399 --> 00:10:33,120
To the pavilion.

247
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:34,120
Come on.

248
00:10:38,720 --> 00:10:39,919
(Storytelling Pavilion)
In the years of old,

249
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:44,320
the Sacred Hand Supreme,
Chu Xianzhi, founded the sect.

250
00:10:44,480 --> 00:10:45,919
He united the Northern Martial World.

251
00:10:46,320 --> 00:10:47,240
His goal was simple.

252
00:10:47,559 --> 00:10:50,240
To keep martial artists
from harming the common folk.

253
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:53,799
After Chu Xianzhi passed,
Chu Zhongtian succeeded him.

254
00:10:53,799 --> 00:10:55,120
Who is this story about?

255
00:10:55,799 --> 00:10:56,720
I've never heard of him.

256
00:10:56,720 --> 00:10:58,080
He carried
on the legacy of his ancestors.

257
00:10:58,080 --> 00:11:01,919
It's about a legendary figure
of the Martial World.

258
00:11:02,720 --> 00:11:05,360
He helped the poor,
punished evil, and upheld goodness.

259
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:07,399
This man

260
00:11:07,799 --> 00:11:10,320
was a beacon of light and righteousness.

261
00:11:10,720 --> 00:11:12,600
The very embodiment
of heroism and justice.

262
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:13,960
In the Gusu region,

263
00:11:14,039 --> 00:11:16,840
thugs preyed upon the innocent
and committed every crime imaginable.

264
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:18,320
The local people

265
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:20,840
suffered a level of misery
that was simply unbearable.

266
00:11:21,360 --> 00:11:24,399
The local authorities
were so intimidated by his power

267
00:11:24,400 --> 00:11:25,600
that they turned a blind eye.

268
00:11:26,039 --> 00:11:27,799
When Chu Zhongtian learned of this,

269
00:11:27,960 --> 00:11:30,559
he decided to teach a lesson

270
00:11:30,919 --> 00:11:33,720
to that wicked Prince of Wu.

271
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:36,320
(Storytelling Pavilion)
Bravo! Well said!

272
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:37,639
Unfortunately,

273
00:11:38,000 --> 00:11:40,679
as heroic as Chu Zhongtian was,

274
00:11:40,840 --> 00:11:43,320
he was not yet the Sacred Hand Supreme.

275
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:46,039
The Four Great Thief Kings of the South,

276
00:11:46,039 --> 00:11:48,759
led by the old scoundrel Dongfang Qing,

277
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:53,080
openly defied
the rules of the Martial Alliance.

278
00:11:53,360 --> 00:11:57,000
This prompted Chu Zhongtian
to head south to warn them,

279
00:11:57,159 --> 00:12:00,879
only to be ambushed by the four kings.

280
00:12:01,120 --> 00:12:04,720
He lost the imperial Sacred Token

281
00:12:05,440 --> 00:12:07,840
and has lived
with that bitter regret ever since.

282
00:12:08,200 --> 00:12:10,559
- Bravo!
- Excellent!

283
00:12:10,559 --> 00:12:12,399
- That was wonderful!
- Well said!

284
00:12:15,039 --> 00:12:15,679
Buyu.

285
00:12:16,080 --> 00:12:17,360
What did you think of that story?

286
00:12:18,159 --> 00:12:18,840
Uncle,

287
00:12:19,240 --> 00:12:20,799
I know why you brought me

288
00:12:20,799 --> 00:12:21,759
to hear this.

289
00:12:22,440 --> 00:12:23,120
Oh, you do?

290
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:25,840
You just wanted me to realize

291
00:12:25,919 --> 00:12:28,159
that the Sacred Hand Sect
acts in the name of justice.

292
00:12:28,480 --> 00:12:29,480
Exactly!

293
00:12:31,399 --> 00:12:32,559
But you're mistaken, Uncle.

294
00:12:34,799 --> 00:12:36,279
I've heard the stories of Master Chu,

295
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:38,559
and while I admire

296
00:12:38,559 --> 00:12:40,000
their chivalrous spirit,

297
00:12:40,679 --> 00:12:41,960
I simply cannot agree with it.

298
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:43,840
As the saying goes,

299
00:12:44,320 --> 00:12:46,039
no matter how much good you do,

300
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:48,039
you cannot place yourself above the law.

301
00:12:48,879 --> 00:12:50,240
Even with ten thousand excuses,

302
00:12:50,879 --> 00:12:52,120
once you break the law,

303
00:12:52,510 --> 00:12:53,759
you must face the consequences.

304
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:56,840
Fair enough.

305
00:12:57,080 --> 00:12:58,200
Fair enough.

306
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:00,159
Uncle,

307
00:13:00,440 --> 00:13:01,279
I have other business

308
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:02,240
to attend to.

309
00:13:02,360 --> 00:13:03,120
All right then.

310
00:13:07,519 --> 00:13:10,240
(How can he be so rigid?)

311
00:13:13,519 --> 00:13:14,120
Wait.

312
00:13:14,575 --> 00:13:15,455
Why are you here?

313
00:13:16,519 --> 00:13:17,559
When it comes to Buyu,

314
00:13:17,799 --> 00:13:19,360
conventional methods won't work.

315
00:13:20,320 --> 00:13:22,440
Here, fresh tea for you.

316
00:13:23,240 --> 00:13:24,080
Stop, thief!

317
00:13:24,720 --> 00:13:25,519
Cursed scoundrel!

318
00:13:25,759 --> 00:13:27,320
I'm the world's greatest constable!

319
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:28,720
Wait for me!

320
00:13:31,519 --> 00:13:32,279
(Mao Buyu.)

321
00:13:32,639 --> 00:13:34,879
(I'll see if you really have
a heart of stone.)

322
00:13:35,480 --> 00:13:36,840
Stop, thief! Stop, thief!

323
00:13:36,860 --> 00:13:37,440
Where are they?

324
00:13:37,440 --> 00:13:38,080
Over there, over there!

325
00:13:38,080 --> 00:13:39,000
- Constable!
- He stole my buns!

326
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,720
The kids stole medicine from my shop!

327
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:41,240
After them!

328
00:13:47,480 --> 00:13:48,080
Thief...

329
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:50,587
Grandma.

330
00:13:51,137 --> 00:13:53,120
Grandma, please eat something.

331
00:13:53,720 --> 00:13:54,960
Aren't you hungry?

332
00:13:55,519 --> 00:13:56,200
Grandma...

333
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:59,000
Grandma.

334
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:03,279
Grandma, are you feeling better?

335
00:14:03,919 --> 00:14:05,879
Get up and play with me, Grandma.

336
00:14:05,879 --> 00:14:07,000
Grandma, wake up.

337
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:09,559
Were you the ones stealing earlier?

338
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:11,519
We're all orphans.

339
00:14:11,519 --> 00:14:13,039
Grandma took us in.

340
00:14:13,240 --> 00:14:14,480
Now Grandma is sick.

341
00:14:14,600 --> 00:14:17,039
The apothecary wouldn't
give us credit and beat us.

342
00:14:17,399 --> 00:14:18,440
Arrest me if you must.

343
00:14:18,637 --> 00:14:21,237
But let me finish brewing
Grandma's medicine first.

344
00:14:23,519 --> 00:14:25,159
You can't take Dabao!

345
00:14:25,399 --> 00:14:26,360
Mr. Constable.

346
00:14:26,360 --> 00:14:27,919
Don't take Dabao.

347
00:14:27,919 --> 00:14:29,879
He needs to take care of Grandma.

348
00:14:29,879 --> 00:14:30,960
Don't take him!

349
00:14:30,960 --> 00:14:32,600
Sir, take me instead.

350
00:14:32,799 --> 00:14:34,399
I'll go in Dabao's place.

351
00:14:38,279 --> 00:14:39,360
Where's the thief?

352
00:14:40,120 --> 00:14:40,759
Thief...

353
00:14:43,480 --> 00:14:44,200
Gao Shun.

354
00:14:45,559 --> 00:14:46,440
Take this money.

355
00:14:46,679 --> 00:14:47,840
Find the best healer.

356
00:14:48,159 --> 00:14:51,039
Use the rest to buy them some food.

357
00:14:51,600 --> 00:14:52,639
But they are thieves.

358
00:14:53,840 --> 00:14:55,159
Keep this between us for now.

359
00:14:55,840 --> 00:14:56,840
I'll handle it.

360
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:00,080
But this doesn't solve the real problem.

361
00:15:00,080 --> 00:15:00,639
But...

362
00:15:01,639 --> 00:15:02,200
Anything

363
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:03,840
can be solved with money.

364
00:15:04,120 --> 00:15:04,879
If it can't,

365
00:15:04,879 --> 00:15:06,039
just pay more.

366
00:15:06,360 --> 00:15:07,600
When it comes to charity,

367
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:09,399
you have to leave it to me.

368
00:15:09,799 --> 00:15:10,639
Here, children.

369
00:15:12,440 --> 00:15:13,080
Take this.

370
00:15:14,799 --> 00:15:15,840
If you ever run out,

371
00:15:16,039 --> 00:15:17,200
come to the Gate Bureau

372
00:15:17,519 --> 00:15:18,960
and find the world's number one...

373
00:15:22,120 --> 00:15:23,720
Future Constable, Luo Wuxia.

374
00:15:24,159 --> 00:15:25,159
I might not have much,

375
00:15:25,159 --> 00:15:26,159
but I have money.

376
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:37,360
I'm off duty tomorrow,

377
00:15:37,830 --> 00:15:39,879
so I want to take Gao Shun
to see the children.

378
00:15:41,639 --> 00:15:42,279
Chang.

379
00:15:42,879 --> 00:15:45,559
I suddenly feel like
my own strength is so small.

380
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:47,279
You've already done so well.

381
00:15:47,279 --> 00:15:48,159
I'm proud of you.

382
00:15:50,960 --> 00:15:51,519
Really?

383
00:15:56,759 --> 00:15:58,480
But I can't be like Luo Wuxia,

384
00:15:58,620 --> 00:15:59,720
and solve Dabao's problems

385
00:15:59,720 --> 00:16:01,799
with a pile of cash
without blinking an eye.

386
00:16:04,279 --> 00:16:06,639
Luo Wuxia provides financial aid,

387
00:16:07,639 --> 00:16:09,600
but you enrich their spirits.

388
00:16:09,919 --> 00:16:11,519
You must realize that

389
00:16:11,919 --> 00:16:14,279
money isn't the only way
to solve problems.

390
00:16:15,279 --> 00:16:16,519
This is what I love about you.

391
00:16:18,620 --> 00:16:20,279
I'll go with you
to see Grandma tomorrow.

392
00:16:20,279 --> 00:16:22,120
We can even bring a healer to treat her.

393
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:23,080
Really?

394
00:16:24,070 --> 00:16:24,919
That would be great.

395
00:16:29,759 --> 00:16:30,639
Hey, stop it.

396
00:16:30,879 --> 00:16:31,960
Everyone is watching.

397
00:16:37,550 --> 00:16:40,825
♪Grudges and regrets
are like strong wine♪

398
00:16:40,863 --> 00:16:43,738
♪Drink it down and let it go♪

399
00:16:44,238 --> 00:16:49,956
♪An empty cup for our love and hate♪

400
00:16:51,138 --> 00:16:54,458
♪Tears blur a fate I can't control♪

401
00:16:54,588 --> 00:16:57,508
♪Let's drink until dawn♪

402
00:16:58,676 --> 00:17:03,916
♪Behind this mask, I'll never lie♪

403
00:17:05,138 --> 00:17:07,531
♪Every reunion feels like the first♪

404
00:17:07,531 --> 00:17:11,181
♪This hidden smile will never fade♪

405
00:17:11,250 --> 00:17:14,740
♪One heart, standing by your side♪

406
00:17:14,838 --> 00:17:17,813
♪To the ends of time♪

407
00:17:17,813 --> 00:17:21,188
♪The moon traces your face♪

408
00:17:21,375 --> 00:17:24,963
♪Draped in clouds, you fill my heart♪

409
00:17:24,963 --> 00:17:31,203
♪To find you
and keep our promise forever♪

410
00:17:31,538 --> 00:17:34,753
♪A silent prayer in my soul♪

411
00:17:35,038 --> 00:17:38,576
♪Carrying my vow beneath the moon♪

412
00:17:38,863 --> 00:17:41,888
♪Hoping we never drift apart again♪

413
00:17:41,888 --> 00:17:44,988
♪On our way to forever♪

414
00:17:44,988 --> 00:17:48,838
♪The moon traces your face♪

415
00:17:48,838 --> 00:17:52,198
♪Draped in clouds, you fill my heart♪

416
00:17:52,388 --> 00:17:58,348
♪To find you
and keep our promise forever♪

417
00:17:59,425 --> 00:18:09,065
♪Just to be with you♪
